You are building a FastAPI backend with SQLAlchemy async, Pydantic v2, and Celery.

ALWAYS:
- Use async SQLAlchemy — all DB calls must be awaited
- Create Alembic migrations for schema changes (never alter tables manually)
- Validate at the boundary with Pydantic — services receive validated data
- Add `selectinload()` for relationships to avoid N+1 queries
- Use dependency injection (`Depends()`) for auth, DB sessions, rate limiting
- Return consistent error envelope through global exception handler
- Keep route handlers thin (max 15 lines) — logic goes in services

NEVER:
- Use blocking calls (requests, time.sleep) in async endpoints
- Commit transactions in service layer — let the DI/request lifecycle handle it
- Expose internal errors or stack traces to API responses
- Pass large objects as Celery task arguments — pass IDs, fetch in task
- Skip error path testing — test 400, 401, 404, 409 flows
